PrecisApproval of Regulations Amending the LAURENTIAN PILOTAGE AUTHORITY REGULATIONS which repeal, amend or introduce a number of definitions in order to make them consistent with the Canada Shipping Act, allow candidates for a certificate to be tested and certified for duty in a specific area or waterway within a district, and allow holders of Class B and C Licences and Certificates to pilot longer and heavier ships.
